Ingress controller

k8s provide two approitech to access k8s micro-service from outside.

1) port fowarding
     1) service ip

     client--NodeIP:NodePort --serviceIp--PodIP
     client--DNS--NodeIP--serviceip-PodIP
     client--DNS--ExternalBalancer---Ingress-controller---workderNodes{1,2}:NodePort--serviceIp--PodIP

Reason to come Ingress
1) ops delay.
2) NodePort remeber
3) community balancer cost increase.
4) application based routing.


Ingress:
 => it is a software define layer 7 loadbalancer.
 => Its k8s level own application layer balancer which basically reduce cose/ops of community balancer (Cloud provider like aws, azure)
 => basically ingress node use nginx service for load balancing.
 => Atleast we should have configure two ingress controller should use in production to provide HA.
 => Ingress controller service(nginx) run as a container over the workerrNodes, this node become ingress controller in kubernetes language.
 => Now ingress controller nodes has to point out external load balancer (one time job).
 => Now rest of rules/work you will put inside ingress controller side. no need to engage external balance team.



